I had booked a 9-10 slot - it was 9:20. If your phlebotomists are taking up appointments every half an hour then you should not give one hour slots to customers in the first place.

A patient is anyway nervous during such tests and about the results. Such behaviour only makes it worse. Requesting you to please give customers an option to choose the gender of the phlebotomist, because clearly your male staff does not know how to behave with women.

The worst experience I have had with any kind of test. Never using PharmEasy again for this.

I hope you will take some further action to improve the experience for future customers, especially women.
